# Clean While Migrating

## Principle

The current codebase was vibe-coded fast. The Payload migration is an opportunity to **clean up adjacent issues** — but only when it is safe and useful, never as a separate big rewrite.

## What to clean

### Do clean (when adjacent to the migration step)
- Duplicated content/data patterns → consolidate into one source
- Dead hardcoded content once the Payload equivalent is seeded and tested
- Inconsistent naming (rename for clarity when migrating that specific feature)
- Unused imports, dead code in files you're already modifying
- Type safety improvements in files you're touching
- Component prop simplification when replacing hardcoded data with Payload data
- Remove Google Sheets CSV fetching logic once content lives in Payload

### Do NOT clean
- Files/features unrelated to the current migration step
- CSS utility classes that still work fine (cinema effects, reveals, etc.)
- Component visual behavior that renders correctly
- Broad "let's rename everything" refactors
- Academic code quality improvements that don't serve the migration

## How to clean

1. **One PR, one feature** — migration + adjacent cleanup in the same PR is fine
2. **Keep diffs small** — if cleanup would make the diff huge, split it into a follow-up
3. **Test after cleaning** — verify the page still renders correctly
4. **Document what was removed** — in the PR description, note what old code was deleted and why
5. **Don't clean ahead** — only clean what the current migration step touches

## Specific cleanup targets

| Current mess | Clean-up approach |
|-------------|-------------------|
| `content.ts` has `POSTER_ITEMS` duplicated for en/fr | Migrate to a single Works collection with localized fields |
| Google Sheets CSV loader (`lib/i18n/sheets.ts`) | Remove once all strings are in Payload globals |
| Fallback TS files (`fallback/en.ts`, `fr.ts`) | Remove once Payload is the source of truth |
| `styles/globals.css` (unused alternate stylesheet) | Delete — only `app/[locale]/globals.css` is active |
| Hardcoded nav items in `Header.tsx` | Replace with Payload Navigation global data |
| Hardcoded footer email in `Footer.tsx` | Replace with Payload ContactInfo global data |
| `base.md` at repo root | Remove if it's just project notes |
| `components.json` referencing wrong CSS path | Fix path or remove if not using shadcn CLI |

## Timing

- Clean AFTER the new Payload equivalent is working
- Never clean BEFORE — keep the old code as a reference until migration is verified
- Remove old code in the same PR that introduces the replacement, or in a dedicated cleanup PR immediately after
